      "native_distribution": "Saskatchewan east to New Brunswick, southwest to Texas, and north to Montana.",
      "native_habitat": "Prairies; open woods; sandy ridges; stream edges. Widely distributed and capable of withstanding a wide range of harsh conditions (one of the most drought resistant oaks) throughout eastern North America; usually found on limestone or calcareous clay.",
